Description:
Amazing space! Gothic Revival meets Neo- modernist design
***INSPECTIONS BY APPOINTMENT ONLY, PLEASE CONTACT AGENT TO PRE-REGISTER***
EXPRESSION OF INTEREST (UNLESS SOLD PRIOR) - CLOSES 11TH AUGUST 5PM
'The Courtyard House': This breathtaking inner-urban sanctuary, designed by owner-architect Ilana Kister, is the inner city's finest residence. Shortlisted in the INDE awards and 2017 Houses awards and featured in the current issue of Habitus, this light-flooded family home flowing to serene courtyards cited on 720sq.m. (approx.), a 17m solar heated/self-dosing lap pool and a spectacular roof garden is linked to the former St Saviour's church, now a gloriously versatile space for large-scale entertaining and home office use. Distinguished by curvilinear timber walls, waxed concrete floors and superior appointments, this unique home constructed on passive energy principles incorporates superbly scaled living and dining areas, 4 double bedrooms (dressing room and ensuite to main), state-of-the-art Miele kitchen and adjoining butler's kitchen, study, luxurious family bathroom, powder room and fitted laundry. Including a 4-car garage and additional parking space, 'The Courtyard House', bordering East Melbourne and close to leading restaurants and cafes, features home automation/Ethernet throughout, hydronic slab heating and air conditioning, custom storage, full security access control and double glazing.
Insights: 6 Oxford Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2017 and 3 other 4 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Boutique style with uninterrupted city views
Tucked away in a secure block of only 6, this second floor abode is a must-see for professionals and investors alike with its generous design, brilliant outlook and premier location with every inner-city advantage at your fingertips. Filled with natural light, the apartment's spotless interior comprises 2 double bedrooms (both with built-in robes) and central bathroom, neat kitchen/meals area and spacious lounge to relax and enjoy the views. Other features include impressively high ceilings, internal laundry facilities, intercom/secure foyer, plus undercover parking space via gated driveway (remote-controlled). Close to everything that counts, cafes and restaurants, shopping precincts, freeway access, trams and trains, Yarra trails and parkland are all within easy reach.

Description:
Melbourne Meets Manhattan
Wow! A boutique New York-style warehouse conversion with its towering ceilings (4.3m), penthouse proportions and stunning renovations, this spectacular Foy & Gibson apartment delivers the ultimate in city-edge style, space and flexibility. A divine mix of modern elegance and industrial edge, the home's vogue interior highlights two extra-large bedrooms (both with fully-fitted robes), sleek central bathroom with Terrazzo tiling and additional powder room (second WC). Add to this an enormous sun-drenched open living/dining area complemented by a superb modern kitchen with Italian marble benchtops/splashbacks, stainless steel cooking appliances and integrated dishwasher. Other features include hydronic heating and split-system a/c, polished floorboards throughout, huge attic storage space, north-facing terrace, plus intercom/secure entry and two parking spaces on title. Stroll to Smith Street cafes and restaurants, shops and supermarkets, Victoria Parade trams and Fitzroy Gardens. Now this is living! Agent; Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
"Barkly House"
Period elegance on the outside, modern function on the inside, "Barkly House" circa 1890 presents an outstanding opportunity to enjoy one of Collingwood's early homes in a prime inner-city lifestyle location just meters from the excitement of Smith Street. Beyond its graceful Hawthorn brick faÃ§ade with distinctive lacework, bay window and magnificent parapet, original features throughout including soaring ceilings and superb ornamental OFPs. At the rear, renovated/extended living/dining spaces with an attractive granite topped kitchen bifold to a north facing garden courtyard doing double time as secure off-street parking for 1 car. Flexible accommodation includes three generous bedrooms, OFPs/BIRs, downstairs lounge/4th bedroom with OFP, study, double shower bathroom, heating, cooling, and alarm.

Description:
Near-City Living in Style
In the stunning contemporary Islington Silos development, a transformation of the site of an historical grain storehouse, this one bedroom apartment offers a lock-up and leave, easy-care lifestyle in a near-city environment.
The as-new interior boasts natural light, open plan living area and city view. The gleaming kitchen is well-equipped with gas cooktop, dishwasher, mirrored splashback and stone benches. Study nook, carpeted bedroom with BIR and Euro laundry are features plus a sparkling, fresh bathroom with shower.
* Secure undercover stacker car space and storage cage
* Communal gym and BBQ area
* Generous balcony
* Heating and cooling
* Walk to Smith, Brunswick and Gertrude Streets retail and eateries
* Bus, city tram and Collingwood Station
* Minutes to Eastern Freeway
Also visit the stand alone website at: www.103-55-65islingtonstreetcollingwood.com
Terms: 10% deposit, balance 30/60 days

Description:
"Inner City Gem"
Near new, this development by prominent Melbourne property developer Urban Inc and designed by award winning architects Elenberg Fraser located in the heart of Collingwood's Foy and Gibson heritage precinct.
Boasting plenty of natural light and amazing views , this spacious 2 bedroom apartment features 2 double bedrooms (BIR's), impressive floor to ceiling windows, open-plan living overlooking entertainment balcony, marvellous stone kitchen, modern bathroom, European laundry, split system, NBN, secure lift access, BBQ area, storage cage and basement car space.
Beyond the apartment, the lush exterior landscapes provide occupants with a secure sanctuary to call home. With plenty of options for entertaining whether it be by the rooftop garden terrace or ,a solar heated plunge pool which overlooks Collingwood's decommissioned industrial factories.
Less than 4km from the CBD and even closer proximity to Smith Street bars/cafes/restaurants, Oxley is conveniently located to provide an ideal balance of work and play.
This is an opportunity you can't miss!

Description:
From Factory To Fabulous
The art on one wall says 'awesome' and the dimensions endorse the message! Converted with an evident respect for its evocative origins as part of the Foy & Gibson factory and warehouse precinct, this stunning apartment projects unique character and irresistible warmth throughout its superb dual level spaces. Original polished floorboards and soaring ceilings define a living/dining area accompanied by a beautifully designed open-plan kitchen while an instantly inviting bedroom with its own bathroom completes the downstairs spaces. A massive main bedroom complemented by a stylish second bathroom defines an upstairs level that emphasizes the undeniable feelgood factor of this fabulous apartment. Secure side by side garaging for two cars and a generous storage cage further enhance the profile of a property in 'Bohemia' - only moments from countless cafes and trams to town.

Description:
A Renovated Classic
At the end of a row of classic brick Victorians, this semi-detached, tuck-pointed cottage boasts a newly updated interior whilst retaining its period allure. With subtle, neutral tones throughout its spacious and light-filled interior, the home comprises 2 generously proportioned bedrooms with BIRs, a sun-drenched formal living room with gaslog fire and B/I bookshelf, well-appointed contemporary kitchen/meals, modern central bathroom with deep bathtub and Euro laundry, powder room and private, paved rear courtyard (ROW). In a quiet location enjoying an idyllic inner-northern lifestyle literally one minute away from The Gem pub and dining, the home is closely located to Edinburgh Gardens, Fitzroy Swimming Pool, vibrant Smith Street transport, cafes and bars and many fine schools. Features include Baltic Pine floors and an original OFP, heating, cost and eco-efficient solar hot water.

Comprising a generous 64.5 sqm of living space plus full-width balcony with panoramic views, the apartment is one of only three on this level of a small-scale boutique development, ensuring exceptional privacy. Description:
The best in townhouse living
Come and explore this exciting opportunity to live in the inner city close to public transport, cafes, bars and nightlife; yet you can retreat to this quiet and private townhouse with only foot traffic outside your front door. This modern two level townhouse and surrounds, on the former Yorkshire Brewery site in Collingwood, is full of surprises. The townhouse itself, introduced by a private ground floor terrace entrance, offers inviting living/dining areas featuring a compact kitchen fitted with premium stone surfaces. Above, two double bedrooms and two bathrooms include a main bedroom served by a stylish ensuite and welcoming balcony. Double glazing, quality appliances and reverse cycle heating/cooling further enhance a residence accompanied by secure parking and residents' facilities including a gym, library/retreat, BBQ area, visitors accommodation, hire cars and bikes, valet laundry and dry cleaning service, full time property manager and a coffee shop right near your door.

Set in an attractive row of charming Victorians just a stroll to Gertrude & Smith Street, Victoria Streets cafes, restaurants, shopping and transport plus East Melbourne Parks/Gardens and MCG close by.

Description:
Hidden behind Heritage!
Filled with northerly light, this third-floor apartment at the rear of one of Collingwood's most iconic buildings makes an ideal city pad or quality addition to any investment portfolio with its generously proportioned layout, quality features and secure surrounds. Set at the rear completely detached from the bustle of Smith Street, the apartment's interior comprises one double bedroom (with built-in robes) and central bathroom, spacious open living/dining area leading out to a fabulous full-width West-facing terrace. Add to this a well-appointed kitchen with dishwasher and stainless steel cooking appliances, neatly positioned laundry, intercom, plus lift to secure entry foyer and lower-level car space (easy access via Little Oxford Street). On the fringe of East Melbourne & Fitzroy it's only walking distance to Victoria Parade trams and Iconic Gertrude, Smith and Brunswick Street lifestyle. Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Family living in convenient quasi cul de sac
This west facing single fronted free standing block fronted weatherboard home is replete with a host of attractive features. From its corrugated iron & tessellated tiled verandah and posts, opening to the wide arched checkerboard entrance hall and open fireplaces and mantles. Boasting central bathroom & laundry, and open living/family, with timber floorboards, timber kitchen, gas cooktop & stainless steel canopy, cupboards below benches, dishwasher, wall oven and ample three quarter height cupboards.
Upstairs is a versatile single room with ensuite bathroom, built in robes, and access into roof space for storage of occasional items, that boasts double doors that open to a timber balcony with easterly aspect.
Numerous period features retained - verandah lacework ornate plaster roses, arched entrance hall, cornices, tiled surrounds to fire places, rose coloured glass, wainscoting, claw foot bath with shower over, and period style light fittings, with plenty of modern creature comforts like hydronic heating, security alarm and split system air conditioning.
Auction Saturday 8th July @ 11.30am
